      • addAccountWith

        public void addAccountWith(java.lang.CharSequence param)
        Appends the specified AccountWith to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used to identify where the funds, by order of the Beneficiary/Remitting Bank are to be remitted. Used when the payment is to be effected to a bank, if defaults are not applicable. For Import L/C's, this will be used to define the either the Reimbursement Banks (THIRD.PARTY.BANK) bank to credit, or the paying/ negotiating bank payment will be made to. For Export L/C's, this will be the remitting bank in accordance with the beneficiaries instructions, payment is to be made. Validation Rules: 4 lines of 1-35 type S (Uppercase alpha or numeric) characters. (Optional input)

        Parameters:
        param - the AccountWith to append
        Returns:
        nothing

      • addChgsClaim

        public void addChgsClaim(TField param)
        Appends the specified ChgsClaim to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field specifies the charges claimed by the Sender, if any. Any code used in this field must be between slashes and must appear at the beginning of a line. Narrative text must not begin with a slash and, if used, must begin on a new line and be the last information in the field. This is used as TAG73A of MT734. This field specifies the charges which have been added to the amount of the drawing for the Message Type MT 750 and represents TAG 73A. This field represents TAG 71D in MT 742. Validation Rules: Valid SWIFT.CODE.WORDS. 1-6 lines of 35 type Z (Alphanumeric) characters.

      • addOverride

        public void addOverride(TField param)
        Appends the specified Override to the end of the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: System maintained field. This field contains all the override messages which the user agreed to during input of the Drawing. The field will be updated by the system and no operator input will be allowed. During the validation of a Drawing contract, the system may provide the user with a series of screen override messages to indicate an anomaly, for instance, that there is no limit set up for the customer. In the event that the user confirms the override, the full text of the actual override message will be stored, for reference purposes only, in this multivalue field. For example, if the user inputs a deal, then when the Drawing is validated a warning bell will sound and a message will appear at the foot of the screen which reads : 'NO LIMIT DEFINED FOR CUSTOMER' This will draw the users attention to the override entry(s). After checking and making any necessary amendments the user then approves the transaction. Validation Rules: This is a multi valued field. Standard T24 alphanumeric field. A maximum of 35 characters may be entered. This is a NOINPUT field.

        Parameters:
        param - the Override to append
        Returns:
        nothing

        Field description: System maintained field. This field contains all the override messages which the user agreed to during input of the Drawing. The field will be updated by the system and no operator input will be allowed. During the validation of a Drawing contract, the system may provide the user with a series of screen override messages to indicate an anomaly, for instance, that there is no limit set up for the customer. In the event that the user confirms the override, the full text of the actual override message will be stored, for reference purposes only, in this multivalue field. For example, if the user inputs a deal, then when the Drawing is validated a warning bell will sound and a message will appear at the foot of the screen which reads : 'NO LIMIT DEFINED FOR CUSTOMER' This will draw the users attention to the override entry(s). After checking and making any necessary amendments the user then approves the transaction. Validation Rules: This is a multi valued field. Standard T24 alphanumeric field. A maximum of 35 characters may be entered. This is a NOINPUT field.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        nothing

      • getAcptTmBand

        public TField getAcptTmBand()
        Returns the AcptTmBand

        Field description: Acceptance period mentioned in LC to which the DRAWING should be adjusted to. Applicable for mixed payment LCs. When mixed payment LCs are input, the operator shall be giving various time bands with the LC to indicate that each portion belongs to a different time band. As documents are received and DRAWINGS are input, the operator is required to input the time band to which this DRAWING should get appropriated. EXAMPLE: - Take a LC record with the following input. LC Record

        DRAW.TYPE: SP
        PAYMENT.PCT:50
        PAY.PORTION: 50,000
        ACPT.TM.BAND:20000606
        DRAW.TYPEAC
        PAYMENT.PCT25
        PAY.PORTION25000
        ACPT.TM.BAND 30
        DRAW.TYPEAC
        PAYMENT.PCT25
        PAY.PORTION25000
        ACPT.TM.BAND 60
        Let us assume that a particular drawing is to be appropriated to the third multivalue set. In such case the ACPT.TM.BAND in DRAWING should be input as 60. This will be understood that this DRAWING is against the third multivale set in LC. For sight and acceptance LCs this will be defaulted to expiry date of the LC Validation Rules: Mandatory Input for mixed payment.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The AcptTmBand

      • getBrokerCode

        public TField getBrokerCode()
        Returns the BrokerCode

        Field description: This field is used either to hold the broker involved with the deal or will contain the method by which the deal was agreed, hence input to this field must be the key to a valid record on either the BROKER file or the FX.DEAL.METHOD table. An agent is a broker or middle man bewteen the import and exporter and earns his fee or commission from the Letter of Credit Drawings amount either as a percentage or flat amount. This flat amount is paid to the agent by the issuing bank at time of drawing. When the BROKER.CODE is changed the remaining broker fields are cleared. When a FX.DEAL.METHOD is entered the broker fields are cleared and become NOINPUT fields. Validation Rules: Must be the key to a valid record on either the BROKER file or the FX.DEAL.METHOD file. Optional Input.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The BrokerCode

      • getBrokerage

        public TField getBrokerage()
        Returns the Brokerage

        Field description: Contains the amount of brokerage to be paid to the broker defined above. Expressed in terms of the deal currency. Input to this field may be in the form of a flat amount or a percentage. To define a percentage append the % to the rate input, and the system will calculate this percentage of the DOCUMENT.AMOUNT. If no value is entered here but a broker code is defined above, then the system will attempt to calculate a default brokerage - firstly using the percentage defined on the underlying Letter of Credit contract, and if not defined using the conditions set up on the BROKER file. If an amount is calculated succesfully the it will be defaulted in this field, and will be expressed in the deal currency. Validation Rules: Standard T24 amount field, expressed in the DRAW.CURRENCY. Input only allowed when a BROKER has been entered in the BROKER.CODE field. Optional input.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The Brokerage

      • getDiscountAmt

        public TField getDiscountAmt()
        Returns the DiscountAmt

        Field description: For Acceptance (AC) or Deferred Payment (DP) drawings, this field indicates that the deal is being discounted and is the amount of discount to be applied to the document amount. If this field is entered, then payment will be made to the beneficiary, on the value date of the drawing, for the document amount minus the discount amount entered here, and minus load amount if any, if the Discount Party Charged is set as Beneficiary. Any charges for the account of the beneficiary will be deducted from the net payment amount (i.e. document amount less discount and load amounts). Similarly, the Reimburse amount will be claimed from the Opener, on the maturity date of the drawing, for the document amount plus the discount amount entered here, and any load amount if any, if the Discount Party Charged is set as Opener. The discount amount will be accrued over the life of the drawing, at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file. Drawings can be discounted in respect of Export/Import Letter of Credit. If the user wishes to enter a discount rate rather than a discount amount, then this can be performed by entering a value in the DISCOUNT.RATE field above. If this is the case, then this field will be calculated and updated by the system. Validation Rules: 1-4 type Amt characters plus a decimal point. Standard Amount Format. (Optional input) Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is 'AC', or 'DP'. If entered, then DISCOUNT.RATE cannot be entered.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The DiscountAmt

      • getDiscountRate

        public TField getDiscountRate()
        Returns the DiscountRate

        Field description: For acceptance (AC) or deferred payment (DP) drawings, this field indicates that the deal is being discounted and contains the rate of discount to be applied. If this field is entered, payment will be made for the DOCUMENT.AMOUNT minus the DISCOUNT.AMT calculated from this rate and also minus load amount if any, where the Discount Party Charged is the Beneficiary. If this field is entered, Reimbursement will be claimed for the DOCUMENT.AMOUNT plus the DISCOUNT.AMT calculated from this rate and also plus load amount if any, where the Discount Party Charged is the Opener. The discount amount will be amortized over the life of the Drawing at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file. Drawings can be discounted on Export or Import Letters of credit. Either a discount rate or a discount amount may be entered. The system will calculate amount when rate is input. Validation Rules: Standard rate format. Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is AC or DP. Cannot be entered if DISCOUNT.AMT is entered.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The DiscountRate

      • getDrawCurrency

        public TField getDrawCurrency()
        Returns the DrawCurrency

        Field description: This field specifies the currency of the drawing. However, should the applicant / opening bank / Beneficiary wish to effect reimbursement in a currency different to that of the drawing, the exchange rate input in the field RATE.BOOKED will be used to convert the DRAW.CURRENCY into DRAWDOWN.ACCOUNT.CURRENCY. If no input is made in RATE.BOOKED, the market foreign exchange rate will be defaulted and the system will automatically convert the draw currency into that of the reimbursement currency (DRAWDOWN ACCOUNT CURRENCY). Also refer help text of field RATE.SPREAD Validation Rules: CCY (Currency code e.g. GBP must be 3 characters). Default to LC.CURRENCY. (Mandatory Input) In the event that both the drawdown account and payment account are different currencies to that of the drawing, the Foreign exchange rate applicable to the drawdown account currency and the DRAW.CURRENCY will be entered in RATE.BOOKED. With regards to payment account a separate Foreign Exchange rate will be entered in TREASURY.RATE field with TREASURY.SPREAD. The rate entered here will be used between DRAW.CURRENCY and PAYMENT.ACCOUNT.CURRENCY.

        Parameters:
        Returns:

      • getDrawdownAccount

        public TField getDrawdownAccount()
        Returns the DrawdownAccount

        Field description: This field identifies the account where funds are to be received from under this drawing. The account which will be debited on either the value date or maturity review date, depending on drawing type, in reimbursement of funds paid to the beneficiary of the drawing. If this field is not entered, then a default will be found from the parent L/C contract. For Import L/C's, this default will come from the APPLICANT.ACC field of the L/C. For Export L/C's, the default will come from the ISSUING.BANK.ACC field of the L/C. If these fields were not entered, and this drawing involves an actual payment, (i.e. drawing types 'AC', 'D',or 'SP'), then a mandatory input is required. For drawing types 'AC', 'DP', this account will be debited on the Maturity Review date in respect of reimbursement. For drawing type 'SP', this account will be debited on the Value date in respect of reimbursement. The currency of this account need not be the same as the currency of the drawing. If this is the case, the system will automatically calculate the amount to be debited (see RATE.BOOKED above). If the Drawing were linked to Shipping Guarantee, then drawdown account will be consider based on Provision netting field If Provision Netting is 'NO' - Irrespective of the account given in Drawdown Account, the Credit Provision Account of the MD is debited to the extent of Provision. For the remaining amount, the Cover Account is debited. The Drawdown account is used only for collecting charges. If Provision Netting is'YES' - Credit provision account of the MD is debited to the extent of provision. For the remaining amount, the drawdown account is debited. Validation Rules: 1-16 Mnemonic characters relating to a Customer Account or a Nostro Account, or any other account. Default from L/C (see below). Mandatory input depending upon type. Mandatory input for drawing types 'AC', 'DP', or 'SP'.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The DrawdownAccount

      • getDrawingType

        public TField getDrawingType()
        Returns the DrawingType

        Field description: This field displays a code to specify what type of drawing this is. This code identifies which kind of Drawing is being made under the L/C, and will impact the kind of processing done. The following types can be entered for a new drawing: AC - Acceptance (Usance credits) DP - Deferred Payment (Usance credits) RP - Release Payment SP - Sight Payment CO - L/C Collection The following types can only be entered as a change to an existing drawing: CC - Collection Chase CR - Collection Rejection FR - Final Rejection MA - Matured Acceptance MD - Matured Deferred Payment. RD - Registration of Documents DC - Document Checking AD-Amendment to drawings (only SP/MA/MD drawings can be amended using AD)

        SG - Shipping guarantee is issued under an import Letter of Credit. Can't be created manually. Draw type can be changed to SP, AC or DP only. For Drawing types of 'AC' and 'DP', a term or usance credit is established whereby the funds will be debited and paid on the MATURITY.REVIEW date specified later. If the funds are required to be paid before this date, the Drawing can be Discounted, whereby payment is made on the Value date specified, but reimbursement is obtained on the MATURITY.REVIEW date. If 'SP' is entered, then both Payment and reimbursement is made on the VALUE.DATE specified. For 'AC' and 'DP' type drawings, once the maturity review date is reached and the drawing undergoes maturity processing, then the Drawing type will automatically change to 'MA' (From 'AC'), and 'MD' (From 'DP'), indicating that these deals are now matured. However, it is to be noted that for Export Usance Drawing to Mature automatically, either the CONFIRM.INST in LC should hold the value as CONFIRM or the Drawing must have been discounted. In absence of either of these the Drawing has to be manually matured. In the case of Import Usance Drawing is maturity is always automatic with an option for the user to manually mature the same. If an authorised 'CO' is changed to a 'CC', then the system will perform chasing logic (ie. produce chase advices), and the reset the drawing type back to its original value, once authorised. When a drawing type of RP is used for an Export LC, this will generate a message (MT754) acknowledging documents were presented in accordance with the terms and conditions of the underlying credit and also a claim for reimbursement (MT742). Alternatively, an Import LC will generate the release of a payment, to the beneficiary, in the form of a Customer Transfer (MT100). A Final Rejection (FR) is normally used when the Sender considers the documents, not to be in accordance with the terms and conditions of the credit, and consequently, refuses them. The difference between drawing type FR and CR is that using type CR will generate a message denoting advice of refusal (MT734) and FR will only ever generate a letter denoting Advice of Refusal/Rejection (1734). Note that this drawing type may only be used following a Collection Rejection (CR). Amendment to Drawing (AD) is permitted to facilitate messaging activity by enabling to alter text and/or local fields.

        When the field REDUCE.LC.LIAB in MD.PARAMETER is set to 'Yes', 'SG' type of Drawings are created under import LC. Can't be created manually. Draw type can be changed to SP, AC or DP only. Note : Neither a type FR or RP will reduce Drawings limits. Validation Rules: 2-2 type AAA (Alpha) characters. Valid codes are: 'AC'; 'DP'; 'RP'; 'SP'; 'CO'; 'CC'; 'CR'; 'FR'; 'MA'; 'MD';'AD'. (Mandatory Input) RP may be used irrespective of the type of the underlying LC. If the type of L/C is a sight payment, then the only valid inputs to this field are:- 'SP', 'CO', 'CC', or 'CR'. If the type of L/C is a usance or term payment, then the only valid inputs to this field are:- 'AC', 'DP', 'CO', 'CC', or 'CR'. 'CR' can only be entered if the drawing has been previously authorised as 'CO'. 'FR' can only be entered if the drawing has previously been authorised as 'CR'. Next stage after registering documents "RD" must be "DC". Draw type "DC" can be changed to "CR","RP","SP","AC","DP" depending upon the LC type

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The DrawingType

      • getGraceDays

        public TField getGraceDays()
        Returns the GraceDays

        Field description: This is a Numeric field and shall be used to input to indicate the additional number of days for which the interest on the discounted drawing is to be recovered. This amount thus calculated for the number of days input in this field, will be in addition to the Discount and Load amount calculated. This field thus represents the cushion that could be made available in the event of the settlement being delayed for a Discounted Drawing. This shall however have no impact on the Maturity Date of the Drawing. Amortization of amount thus collected shall take place only till the MATURITY.REVIEW date or the NEW.MATURITY.DATE as input. In the event of such Discounted Drawing being extended using DR.DISC.AMENDMENTS, the amortization shall take place till the NEW.MATURITY.DATE. However, if the same is matured online or back-dated, then the amortization would have taken place only till such date. The input in this field is permitted only at the first instance of discounting a Drawing. The field opens up only if the Discount/Load rate is input. Validation Rules: Numeric field.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The GraceDays

        Field description: Contains the Load amount accrued to date, if the drawing has been discounted and a Load amount/rate specified, expressed in local currency. The field will be calculated by the system and no operator input will be allowed. Every time the Load amount is accrued in the end of day, this field is automatically updated to show the total amount accrued to date, converted to local currency. Validation Rules: System Generated. 1-14 (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LdAmrtDteLcy

      • getLimitReference

        public TField getLimitReference()
        Returns the LimitReference

        Field description: This field will identify the LIMIT.REFERENCE number to be checked for limit control on L/C transactions. Each Drawing transaction will be checked against the LIMIT file to verify the availability of a limit facility. If no input is made at this field, the LIMIT system will provide a default according to the values defined in the LIMIT.PARAMETER file. If required, more details can be found in the LIMIT user guide. A Sight drawing / Maturing Acceptance or Deferred Payment will result in the limit availability being increased by the amount of the payment. An Acceptance / Deferred Payment drawing will not impact the limit utilisation until its maturity. Note : The customer that limits will be checked against is the customer defined in CON.CUS.LINK (defined on the L/C record). Validation Rules: 3-7 numeric characters. Input to this field must be a valid LIMIT.REFERENCE number. If no limit exists for the customer, a corresponding error message will be displayed by the system with an override facility.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LimitReference

      • getLiquidationMode

        public TField getLiquidationMode()
        Returns the LiquidationMode

        Field description: This field identifies the manner in which overdue payments are handled. The default for all contracts is AUTOMATIC. Three options are currently available: AUTOMATIC, SEMI-AUTOMATIC, and MANUAL AUTOMATIC indicates that payments will be settled irrespective of whether funds are available in the drawdown account. SEMI-AUTOMATIC indicates that a payment will be made only if funds are available, and that a PD end of day process will regularly attempt to make payment by checking whether funds have become available. MANUAL indicates that the contract will only settle if funds are available and that any future settlement of outstanding payments must be made manually via the PD module. Validation Rules: If the PD product is not defined for the current company then the only allowed setting is AUTOMATIC.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LiquidationMode

      • getLoadAmount

        public TField getLoadAmount()
        Returns the LoadAmount

        Field description: Optional and only allowed if DISCOUNT.RATE or DISCOUNT.AMOUNT is present. This field together with DISCOUNT.AMT gives the total amount that the Document amount is to be discounted by, which should not exceed the document amount. If this field is entered, then payment will be made to the beneficiary, on the value date of the drawing, for the document amount minus the discount amount entered above, and the load amount entered here, if the Discount Party Charged is Beneficiary. Any charges for the account of the beneficiary will be deducted the net payment amount (i.e. document amount less discount and load amounts). Similarly, the reimbursement would be claimed for the document amount plus the discount amount entered above, and the load amount entered here, if the Discount Party Charged is Opener. The load amount will be accrued over the life of the drawing, at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file, separately from the discount amount. Drawings can be discounted in respect of Export/Import Letter of Credit. If the user wishes to enter a load rate rather than a load amount, then this can be performed by entering a value in the LOAD.RATE field above. Validation Rules: 1-14 type AMT (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point. Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is 'AC', or 'DP' and DISCOUNT.RATE, or DISCOUNT.AMT has been entered. If entered, then LOAD.RATE cannot be entered.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LoadAmount

      • getLoadAmtLocal

        public TField getLoadAmtLocal()
        Returns the LoadAmtLocal

        Field description: The value in this field contains the local currency equivalent of the LOAD.AMT, if this amount has been entered. The field will be calculated by the system and no operator input will be allowed. When the deal is input, the local currency equivalent of the load amount will be calculated by the system using the mid market spot rate in effect at the time. Validation Rules: System Generated. 1-14 (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LoadAmtLocal

      • getLoadRate

        public TField getLoadRate()
        Returns the LoadRate

        Field description: Allowed if DISCOUNT.RATE or DISCOUNT.AMOUNT is present. This field together with DISCOUNT.RATE gives the total rate that the Document amount is to be discounted by which should not exceed 100%. If this field is entered, then payment will be made to the beneficiary, on the value date of the drawing, for the document amount minus the discount amount calculated from the discount rate entered above, and the load amount calculated from the rate entered here, if the Discount Party Charged is Beneficiary. Any charges for the account of the beneficiary will be deducted the net payment amount (i.e. document amount less discount and load amounts). Similarly, if the reimburse were to be claimed from the Opener, the same is done for the document amount plus the discount amount calculated from the discount rate entered above, and the load amount calculated from the rate entered here, if the Discount Party Charged is Opener. The load amount will be accrued over the life of the drawing, at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file, separately from the discount amount. Drawings can be discounted in respect of Export/Import Letter of Credit. If the user wishes to enter a load amount rather than a load rate, then this can be performed by entering a value in the LOAD.AMT field below. Validation Rules: Standard rate format (Only up to 6 integer and decimal characters). (Optional input) Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is 'AC', or 'DP' and DISCOUNT.RATE or DISCOUNT.AMT has been entered. If entered, then LOAD.AMT cannot be entered.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LoadRate

      • getMaturityReview

        public TField getMaturityReview()
        Returns the MaturityReview

        Field description: This field contains the date on which Acceptance/Deferred Payment drawings will mature, or Letter of Credit Collection drawings will be due for chasing. For Sight drawings this field is to be used when Discounted, indicating the date up to which interest is to be calculated, when a rate is input. However, this field can be input only when DR.DEBIT.TO.CUST is set to NOTDEBITED for Sight Drawings. When a term/usance drawing is entered, the date in this field will be the date that maturity entries will be generated, and limits liquidated. These entries will be generated at the end of day on the date entered. For L/C Collection, this date will be used for chasing and following up the fate of the drawing. There will be an end of day report produced which which will list all collection type drawings that have passed their Maturity Review date. Validation Rules: Standard Date Format. Mandatory for drawing types: 'AC', 'DP', 'CO', 'CC'. Mandatory when Sight Drawing is discounted. No input allowed for drawing type 'SP' when not discounted. If a 'CO' is changed to a 'CC', then the user is requested to change this maturity review date to indicate the date the drawing should next be chased.

      • getOverride

        public List<TField> getOverride()
        Returns the collection of Override

        Field description: System maintained field. This field contains all the override messages which the user agreed to during input of the Drawing. The field will be updated by the system and no operator input will be allowed. During the validation of a Drawing contract, the system may provide the user with a series of screen override messages to indicate an anomaly, for instance, that there is no limit set up for the customer. In the event that the user confirms the override, the full text of the actual override message will be stored, for reference purposes only, in this multivalue field. For example, if the user inputs a deal, then when the Drawing is validated a warning bell will sound and a message will appear at the foot of the screen which reads : 'NO LIMIT DEFINED FOR CUSTOMER' This will draw the users attention to the override entry(s). After checking and making any necessary amendments the user then approves the transaction. Validation Rules: This is a multi valued field. Standard T24 alphanumeric field. A maximum of 35 characters may be entered. This is a NOINPUT field.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        List<TField> -

      • getPaymentAccount

        public TField getPaymentAccount()
        Returns the PaymentAccount

        Field description: This field identifies the account where funds are to be paid to under this drawing. The account which will be credited on either the value date or maturity review date, depending on drawing type, for the payment in respect of the drawing. If the payment method entered above is either 'BP' (Bankers payment) or 'CH' (Cheque), then this field will be automatically updated by the system to indicate the account to be used. This will be set up on the LC.PARAMETERS file as 'B.P.ISSUED.ACC' and 'CHEQUES.ISSUE.ACC'. For drawing types 'AC', 'DP', this account will be credited on the Maturity Review date in respect of payment, unless the drawing is being discounted, in which case it will be credited on the value date. For drawing type 'SP', this account will be credited on the Value date in respect of payment. For drawing type 'CO' with 'UNDER.RESERVE' set to 'YES', then this account will be credited on the value date. Validation Rules: 1-16 Mnemonic characters relating to a Customer Account or a Nostro Account, or any other account. Default from Payment Method (see below). Mandatory input for Drawing types 'AC', 'DP', 'SP', and 'CO' with UNDER.RESERVE set to 'YES'.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The PaymentAccount

      • getPaymentMethod

        public TField getPaymentMethod()
        Returns the PaymentMethod

        Field description: This field identifies the method of payment for the drawing. Used to determine which payment method is to be used in order to effect payment to the Beneficiary for Export L/C's, or the Negotiating Bank or Reimbursing bank for Import L/C's. Valid codes are: N - Pay through a Nostro account BP - Issue a Bankers Payment drawn on a Nostro account. CH - Issue a Cheque, drawn on a Nostro account IT - Pay to an Internal Account If the method chosen is 'N', then payment will be made via a Nostro account, entered in the field below PAYMENT.ACCOUNT, with advices. Validation Rules: 'N' or 'BP' or 'CH' or 'IT'. (Mandatory Input)

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The PaymentMethod

      • getPayresParty

        public TField getPayresParty()
        Returns the PayresParty

        Field description: This field cannot be input. It defaults to the party mentioned in the RISK.PARTY field of the Discrepant type chosen above. Eg : If the RISK.PARTY field in the DISCREPANT.TYPE table is PRESENTOR then the Presentor Customer number is defaulted as the PAYRES.PARTY or if the field has ISSUING.BANK as the RISK.PARTY then, the Issuing bank is defaulted as the PAYRES.PARTY. Explanation : The ultimate purpose of setting this field is to identify the actual Risk party of the particular transaction. Once this field is set, a separate Drawing Limit is hit for the party in this field and a contingent entry is raised for the party with type as PAYRES. Once the documents under collection are Accepted by the ISSUING.BANK, the Limits are reversed and the Contingent entry raised is also reversed and the normal flow continues from there on. Validation Rules: : It is a No input field. Defaults to the value in RISK.PARTY field in the DISCREPANT.TYPE chosen.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The PayresParty

      • getProvAmtRel

        public TField getProvAmtRel()
        Returns the ProvAmtRel

        Field description: This field is used to display the provision amount released on account of this DRAWING. Generally will be defaulted by the system based on the percentage of PROVISION input in LC. This will be in the currency in which the provision is held ( Provision credit account currency in LC contract). The field can also be input by the user as to the amount required to be released on account of this DRAWING. Validation Rules: Optional input. When input the amount will be checked with the provision percentage in LC and an error will be returned if the amount released exceeds the calculated amount. For calculation of the credit currency equivalent the following rules will be used. : The percentage in LC record is referred and the maximum release amount is determined. The amount determined is converted to credit provision currency using the current cross rate or mid rate.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The ProvAmtRel

      • getProvNetting

        public TField getProvNetting()
        Returns the ProvNetting

        Field description: Determines whether proportionate provision amount released is to be netted with Drawings amount at the time of settlement of Drawings. Drawings payment entries will be netted only when Drawings and Credit provision account currencies are the same. Override message will be generated when these currencies differ and PROV.NETTING field value will be changed to "NO" when override is accepted. Example: LC Amount USD 100,000; Provision Percentage 20%; Provision Amount USD 20,000 Drawings Amount USD 50,000; Provision Netting Yes.

        DrCredit Provision AccountUSD 10,000
        Dr Drawdown AccountUSD 40,000
        CrPayment Account

        USD 50,000

        Validation Rules: Defaulted from PROV.NETTING field in LC.PARAMETERS. User can amend the defaulted value. Applicable only for LC's with provision.

        public TField getRateBooked()

        Field description: This field displays the exchange rate quoted by the treasury department to the trade finance department (ie excluding department spread). When the document currency <DRAW.CURRENCY> and debit account currency <DRAWDOWN.ACCOUNT.CURRENCY> differ, the user will be able to insert an exchange rate to be applied <DEBIT.CUST.RATE>. This <DEBIT.CUST.RATE> can be derived from the departmental spread indicated in <RATE.SPREAD> and the treasury rate displayed in this <RATE.BOOKED> field.       • getReasonNonPymt

        public TField getReasonNonPymt()
        Returns the ReasonNonPymt

        Field description: This field specifies the reason for non-payment. This is a Mandatory field in the MT744 message. This field corresponds to field 73R in the messages. Note: When this field and DISP.OF.CLAIM are inputted, the MT744 message will be generated. Valid Codes: DIFF Different claiming bank. DUPL Duplicate claim. INSU Insufficient information in the claim (for example, payment instruction in complete, shipment data missing). NAUT Not authorised by Issuing Bank to reimburse. OTHR Any other reason which must be specified in the text (2nd subfield). OVER Total claim exceeds maximum documentary credit amount (exceed any additional amounts covered). REFE Refer to Issuing Bank for further instructions. TTNA TT claim not allowed. WINF Information stated in the claim differ from the R/A. XAMT Total claim exceeds available documentary credit amount (sum of maximum credit amount and additional amounts covered). Validation Rules: 4!c*35 line and accept Z (Alphanumeric) characters.

      • getTraceDate

        public TField getTraceDate()
        Returns the TraceDate

        Field description: This field is applicable only to documentary collections and indicate the date the collection should be chased. Accepts Standard date format. Holds the Scheduled date on which a Tracer message has to be sent. If the date is some future date, then an EB.FREE.MESSAGE record is produced on authorization of the DRAWING which holds the Tracer message and relevant details of the particular transaction with the scheduled date on which it has to be sent. If the date is TODAY then the Tracer message is sent during End of Day. Validation Rules: Mandatory when Draw Type is 'CO' Will get cycled only if EB.FREE.PARAMETERS is set up.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The TraceDate

      • getTreasuryRate

        public TField getTreasuryRate()
        Returns the TreasuryRate

        Field description: This is an exchange rate between the document currency and the credit account currency. This is the rate quoted by the treasury department to the trade finance department excluding departmental spread. The department spread will be accepted in CUSTOMER.SPREAD field. The exchange rate including the rate spread will be customer credit rate and will be shown in CREDIT.CUST.RATE field. THE CREDIT.CUST.RATE will be applied between the document currency and the credit account currency (DRAW.CURRENCY and PAYMENT.ACCOUNT.CURRENCY) if they differ. Default calculated from currency table, using current mid market spot rate. Validation Rules: Standard Rate format (Only up to 6 integer and decimal characters) (Optional Input). Input to this field is only allowed if the payment account is in a different currency to the draw currency. Mainly used in export transactions, when the exporter's credit account is in a different currency to the document currency.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The TreasuryRate

      • getTrustRel

        public TField getTrustRel()
        Returns the TrustRel

        Field description: This field is activated for CO type drawings under import Letter Of Credits. The valid values accepted are RELEASE, ACCEPT and REJECT. When this field is set to RELEASE, the system updates the trust limit and LC limit will be reversed back for the document amount. The static fields in Letter Of Credit will also be updated. The system also creates a contingent entry TRCOLL instead of COLL when the documents are set under REJECT. The system also defaults the draw type to be input by the user when he accepts the documents based on the LC type. In case of mixed payments user has to input the draw type and ACPT.TM.BAND field. When the documents are accepted, the user can change the draw type in the Drawing to AC or SP or DP (the value should be in NEW.DRAW.SET) the system automatically updates the TRUST.REL field as ACCEPT. Also the system reverses out the previous limits and contingent entries are creates new limit and contingent entry. When the user changes the draw type from CO to CR, this field is automatically set to REJECT thus reversing all the entries and limits created previously. The valid values accepted are : RELEASE, ACCEPT and REJECT

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The TrustRel

      • getUnconfirmedAmt

        public TField getUnconfirmedAmt()
        Returns the UnconfirmedAmt

        Field description: When a Drawing is done under a partially confirmed Letter of Credit, the User has the option of defining the extent of liquidation under the Unconfirmed portion, which is input here. The input however cannot exceed the total amount unconfirmed under the Letter of Credit outstanding at that point of time. The sum of Confirmed and the Unconfirmed portion should be equal to the Document amount or the Liability amount whichever is lower. Validation Rules: Standard amount format. Mandatory when LC is partially confirmed. Automatically populated by the system when confirmed portion is entered.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The UnconfirmedAmt

      • getUnderReserve

        public TField getUnderReserve()
        Returns the UnderReserve

        Field description: Applicable for Letter of Credit collection ('CO') drawings, when the documents are sent on a collection basis, because of discrepancies, but the drawing is paid to the benefiary "under reserve". This field indicates if payment for the drawing is made under reserve which enables funds paid to the beneficiary to be claimed back by the bank in the event that the documentation is refused by Opening Bank/Applicant due to discrepancies. This can only be entered if the drawing type is 'CO' and is an Export L/C, Payment will be effected on the value date of the drawing. Validation Rules: 'Y' or 'N'. Default 'N' Only allowed for drawing type 'CO', and Export L/C's.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The UnderReserve

        public TField getValueDate()
        Returns the ValueDate

        Field description: This field contains the value date for drawing entries. Can be future or back valued. Cannot be greater than the Maturity Review date.

      • insertOverride

        public void insertOverride(java.lang.CharSequence param, int pos)
        Insert the specified Override to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: System maintained field. This field contains all the override messages which the user agreed to during input of the Drawing. The field will be updated by the system and no operator input will be allowed. During the validation of a Drawing contract, the system may provide the user with a series of screen override messages to indicate an anomaly, for instance, that there is no limit set up for the customer. In the event that the user confirms the override, the full text of the actual override message will be stored, for reference purposes only, in this multivalue field. For example, if the user inputs a deal, then when the Drawing is validated a warning bell will sound and a message will appear at the foot of the screen which reads : 'NO LIMIT DEFINED FOR CUSTOMER' This will draw the users attention to the override entry(s). After checking and making any necessary amendments the user then approves the transaction. Validation Rules: This is a multi valued field. Standard T24 alphanumeric field. A maximum of 35 characters may be entered. This is a NOINPUT field.

        Parameters:
        param - the Override to append
        pos - The position where to insert the value.
        Returns:
        nothing

      • removeOverride

        public void removeOverride(int idx)
        Remove the Override at the specified position in this collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: System maintained field. This field contains all the override messages which the user agreed to during input of the Drawing. The field will be updated by the system and no operator input will be allowed. During the validation of a Drawing contract, the system may provide the user with a series of screen override messages to indicate an anomaly, for instance, that there is no limit set up for the customer. In the event that the user confirms the override, the full text of the actual override message will be stored, for reference purposes only, in this multivalue field. For example, if the user inputs a deal, then when the Drawing is validated a warning bell will sound and a message will appear at the foot of the screen which reads : 'NO LIMIT DEFINED FOR CUSTOMER' This will draw the users attention to the override entry(s). After checking and making any necessary amendments the user then approves the transaction. Validation Rules: This is a multi valued field. Standard T24 alphanumeric field. A maximum of 35 characters may be entered. This is a NOINPUT field.

        Parameters:
        idx - index of the element to remove
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setAcptTmBand

        public void setAcptTmBand(TField value)
        Set the specified value for AcptTmBand
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Acceptance period mentioned in LC to which the DRAWING should be adjusted to. Applicable for mixed payment LCs. When mixed payment LCs are input, the operator shall be giving various time bands with the LC to indicate that each portion belongs to a different time band. As documents are received and DRAWINGS are input, the operator is required to input the time band to which this DRAWING should get appropriated. EXAMPLE: - Take a LC record with the following input. LC Record

        DRAW.TYPE: SP
        PAYMENT.PCT:50
        PAY.PORTION: 50,000
        ACPT.TM.BAND:20000606
        DRAW.TYPEAC
        PAYMENT.PCT25
        PAY.PORTION25000
        ACPT.TM.BAND 30
        DRAW.TYPEAC
        PAYMENT.PCT25
        PAY.PORTION25000
        ACPT.TM.BAND 60
        Let us assume that a particular drawing is to be appropriated to the third multivalue set. In such case the ACPT.TM.BAND in DRAWING should be input as 60. This will be understood that this DRAWING is against the third multivale set in LC. For sight and acceptance LCs this will be defaulted to expiry date of the LC Validation Rules: Mandatory Input for mixed payment.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setBrokerCode

        public void setBrokerCode(TField value)
        Set the specified value for BrokerCode
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used either to hold the broker involved with the deal or will contain the method by which the deal was agreed, hence input to this field must be the key to a valid record on either the BROKER file or the FX.DEAL.METHOD table. An agent is a broker or middle man bewteen the import and exporter and earns his fee or commission from the Letter of Credit Drawings amount either as a percentage or flat amount. This flat amount is paid to the agent by the issuing bank at time of drawing. When the BROKER.CODE is changed the remaining broker fields are cleared. When a FX.DEAL.METHOD is entered the broker fields are cleared and become NOINPUT fields. Validation Rules: Must be the key to a valid record on either the BROKER file or the FX.DEAL.METHOD file. Optional Input.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setBrokerage

        public void setBrokerage(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for Brokerage
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Contains the amount of brokerage to be paid to the broker defined above. Expressed in terms of the deal currency. Input to this field may be in the form of a flat amount or a percentage. To define a percentage append the % to the rate input, and the system will calculate this percentage of the DOCUMENT.AMOUNT. If no value is entered here but a broker code is defined above, then the system will attempt to calculate a default brokerage - firstly using the percentage defined on the underlying Letter of Credit contract, and if not defined using the conditions set up on the BROKER file. If an amount is calculated succesfully the it will be defaulted in this field, and will be expressed in the deal currency. Validation Rules: Standard T24 amount field, expressed in the DRAW.CURRENCY. Input only allowed when a BROKER has been entered in the BROKER.CODE field. Optional input.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        public void setChgsDeduct(TField param, int idx)
        Set the specified ChgsDeduct to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used to specify the charges which have been deducted, by the Sender of the message, from the total amount advised. One or more of the following codes may be used, followed by the currency code and amount: AGENT Agent's commission TELECHAR Teletransmission charges COMM Our commission CORCOM Our correspondent's commission DISC Commercial discount INSUR Insurance premium POST Our postage STAMP Stamp duty WAREHOUS Wharfing and warehouse Any code used in this field must be between slashes and must appear at the beginning of a line. Narrative text must not begin with a slash and, if used, must begin on a new line and be the last information in the field. This is used to map to Tag 71B of MT742, MT750, MT752 and MT754. Validation Rules: Valid SWIFT.CODE.WORDS with MESSAGE.TYPE as 71B. 1-6 lines of 35 type A (Alphanumeric) characters. Accept Z (Alphanumeric) characters when a MT742/750/752/754 is generated.

        Parameters:

        idx - the position in collection

      • setDiscountAmt

        public void setDiscountAmt(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for DiscountAmt
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: For Acceptance (AC) or Deferred Payment (DP) drawings, this field indicates that the deal is being discounted and is the amount of discount to be applied to the document amount. If this field is entered, then payment will be made to the beneficiary, on the value date of the drawing, for the document amount minus the discount amount entered here, and minus load amount if any, if the Discount Party Charged is set as Beneficiary. Any charges for the account of the beneficiary will be deducted from the net payment amount (i.e. document amount less discount and load amounts). Similarly, the Reimburse amount will be claimed from the Opener, on the maturity date of the drawing, for the document amount plus the discount amount entered here, and any load amount if any, if the Discount Party Charged is set as Opener. The discount amount will be accrued over the life of the drawing, at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file. Drawings can be discounted in respect of Export/Import Letter of Credit. If the user wishes to enter a discount rate rather than a discount amount, then this can be performed by entering a value in the DISCOUNT.RATE field above. If this is the case, then this field will be calculated and updated by the system. Validation Rules: 1-4 type Amt characters plus a decimal point. Standard Amount Format. (Optional input) Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is 'AC', or 'DP'. If entered, then DISCOUNT.RATE cannot be entered.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDiscountAmt

        public void setDiscountAmt(TField value)
        Set the specified value for DiscountAmt
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: For Acceptance (AC) or Deferred Payment (DP) drawings, this field indicates that the deal is being discounted and is the amount of discount to be applied to the document amount. If this field is entered, then payment will be made to the beneficiary, on the value date of the drawing, for the document amount minus the discount amount entered here, and minus load amount if any, if the Discount Party Charged is set as Beneficiary. Any charges for the account of the beneficiary will be deducted from the net payment amount (i.e. document amount less discount and load amounts). Similarly, the Reimburse amount will be claimed from the Opener, on the maturity date of the drawing, for the document amount plus the discount amount entered here, and any load amount if any, if the Discount Party Charged is set as Opener. The discount amount will be accrued over the life of the drawing, at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file. Drawings can be discounted in respect of Export/Import Letter of Credit. If the user wishes to enter a discount rate rather than a discount amount, then this can be performed by entering a value in the DISCOUNT.RATE field above. If this is the case, then this field will be calculated and updated by the system. Validation Rules: 1-4 type Amt characters plus a decimal point. Standard Amount Format. (Optional input) Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is 'AC', or 'DP'. If entered, then DISCOUNT.RATE cannot be entered.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDiscountRate

        public void setDiscountRate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for DiscountRate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: For acceptance (AC) or deferred payment (DP) drawings, this field indicates that the deal is being discounted and contains the rate of discount to be applied. If this field is entered, payment will be made for the DOCUMENT.AMOUNT minus the DISCOUNT.AMT calculated from this rate and also minus load amount if any, where the Discount Party Charged is the Beneficiary. If this field is entered, Reimbursement will be claimed for the DOCUMENT.AMOUNT plus the DISCOUNT.AMT calculated from this rate and also plus load amount if any, where the Discount Party Charged is the Opener. The discount amount will be amortized over the life of the Drawing at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file. Drawings can be discounted on Export or Import Letters of credit. Either a discount rate or a discount amount may be entered. The system will calculate amount when rate is input. Validation Rules: Standard rate format. Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is AC or DP. Cannot be entered if DISCOUNT.AMT is entered.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDiscountRate

        public void setDiscountRate(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for DiscountRate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: For acceptance (AC) or deferred payment (DP) drawings, this field indicates that the deal is being discounted and contains the rate of discount to be applied. If this field is entered, payment will be made for the DOCUMENT.AMOUNT minus the DISCOUNT.AMT calculated from this rate and also minus load amount if any, where the Discount Party Charged is the Beneficiary. If this field is entered, Reimbursement will be claimed for the DOCUMENT.AMOUNT plus the DISCOUNT.AMT calculated from this rate and also plus load amount if any, where the Discount Party Charged is the Opener. The discount amount will be amortized over the life of the Drawing at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file. Drawings can be discounted on Export or Import Letters of credit. Either a discount rate or a discount amount may be entered. The system will calculate amount when rate is input. Validation Rules: Standard rate format. Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is AC or DP. Cannot be entered if DISCOUNT.AMT is entered.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field specifies the currency of the drawing. With regards to payment account a separate Foreign Exchange rate will be entered in TREASURY.RATE field with TREASURY.SPREAD. The rate entered here will be used between DRAW.CURRENCY and PAYMENT.ACCOUNT.CURRENCY.

      • setDrawdownAccount

        public void setDrawdownAccount(TField value)
        Set the specified value for DrawdownAccount
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field identifies the account where funds are to be received from under this drawing. The account which will be debited on either the value date or maturity review date, depending on drawing type, in reimbursement of funds paid to the beneficiary of the drawing. If this field is not entered, then a default will be found from the parent L/C contract. For Import L/C's, this default will come from the APPLICANT.ACC field of the L/C. For Export L/C's, the default will come from the ISSUING.BANK.ACC field of the L/C. If these fields were not entered, and this drawing involves an actual payment, (i.e. drawing types 'AC', 'D',or 'SP'), then a mandatory input is required. For drawing types 'AC', 'DP', this account will be debited on the Maturity Review date in respect of reimbursement. For drawing type 'SP', this account will be debited on the Value date in respect of reimbursement. The currency of this account need not be the same as the currency of the drawing. If this is the case, the system will automatically calculate the amount to be debited (see RATE.BOOKED above). If the Drawing were linked to Shipping Guarantee, then drawdown account will be consider based on Provision netting field If Provision Netting is 'NO' - Irrespective of the account given in Drawdown Account, the Credit Provision Account of the MD is debited to the extent of Provision. For the remaining amount, the Cover Account is debited. The Drawdown account is used only for collecting charges. If Provision Netting is'YES' - Credit provision account of the MD is debited to the extent of provision. For the remaining amount, the drawdown account is debited. Validation Rules: 1-16 Mnemonic characters relating to a Customer Account or a Nostro Account, or any other account. Default from L/C (see below). Mandatory input depending upon type. Mandatory input for drawing types 'AC', 'DP', or 'SP'.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDrawingType

        public void setDrawingType(TField value)
        Set the specified value for DrawingType
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field displays a code to specify what type of drawing this is. This code identifies which kind of Drawing is being made under the L/C, and will impact the kind of processing done. The following types can be entered for a new drawing: AC - Acceptance (Usance credits) DP - Deferred Payment (Usance credits) RP - Release Payment SP - Sight Payment CO - L/C Collection The following types can only be entered as a change to an existing drawing: CC - Collection Chase CR - Collection Rejection FR - Final Rejection MA - Matured Acceptance MD - Matured Deferred Payment. RD - Registration of Documents DC - Document Checking AD-Amendment to drawings (only SP/MA/MD drawings can be amended using AD)

        SG - Shipping guarantee is issued under an import Letter of Credit. Can't be created manually. Draw type can be changed to SP, AC or DP only. For Drawing types of 'AC' and 'DP', a term or usance credit is established whereby the funds will be debited and paid on the MATURITY.REVIEW date specified later. If the funds are required to be paid before this date, the Drawing can be Discounted, whereby payment is made on the Value date specified, but reimbursement is obtained on the MATURITY.REVIEW date. If 'SP' is entered, then both Payment and reimbursement is made on the VALUE.DATE specified. For 'AC' and 'DP' type drawings, once the maturity review date is reached and the drawing undergoes maturity processing, then the Drawing type will automatically change to 'MA' (From 'AC'), and 'MD' (From 'DP'), indicating that these deals are now matured. However, it is to be noted that for Export Usance Drawing to Mature automatically, either the CONFIRM.INST in LC should hold the value as CONFIRM or the Drawing must have been discounted. In absence of either of these the Drawing has to be manually matured. In the case of Import Usance Drawing is maturity is always automatic with an option for the user to manually mature the same. If an authorised 'CO' is changed to a 'CC', then the system will perform chasing logic (ie. produce chase advices), and the reset the drawing type back to its original value, once authorised. When a drawing type of RP is used for an Export LC, this will generate a message (MT754) acknowledging documents were presented in accordance with the terms and conditions of the underlying credit and also a claim for reimbursement (MT742). Alternatively, an Import LC will generate the release of a payment, to the beneficiary, in the form of a Customer Transfer (MT100). A Final Rejection (FR) is normally used when the Sender considers the documents, not to be in accordance with the terms and conditions of the credit, and consequently, refuses them. The difference between drawing type FR and CR is that using type CR will generate a message denoting advice of refusal (MT734) and FR will only ever generate a letter denoting Advice of Refusal/Rejection (1734). Note that this drawing type may only be used following a Collection Rejection (CR). Amendment to Drawing (AD) is permitted to facilitate messaging activity by enabling to alter text and/or local fields.

        When the field REDUCE.LC.LIAB in MD.PARAMETER is set to 'Yes', 'SG' type of Drawings are created under import LC. Can't be created manually. Draw type can be changed to SP, AC or DP only. Note : Neither a type FR or RP will reduce Drawings limits. Validation Rules: 2-2 type AAA (Alpha) characters. Valid codes are: 'AC'; 'DP'; 'RP'; 'SP'; 'CO'; 'CC'; 'CR'; 'FR'; 'MA'; 'MD';'AD'. (Mandatory Input) RP may be used irrespective of the type of the underlying LC. If the type of L/C is a sight payment, then the only valid inputs to this field are:- 'SP', 'CO', 'CC', or 'CR'. If the type of L/C is a usance or term payment, then the only valid inputs to this field are:- 'AC', 'DP', 'CO', 'CC', or 'CR'. 'CR' can only be entered if the drawing has been previously authorised as 'CO'. 'FR' can only be entered if the drawing has previously been authorised as 'CR'. Next stage after registering documents "RD" must be "DC". Draw type "DC" can be changed to "CR","RP","SP","AC","DP" depending upon the LC type

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setDrawingType

        public void setDrawingType(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for DrawingType
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field displays a code to specify what type of drawing this is. This code identifies which kind of Drawing is being made under the L/C, and will impact the kind of processing done. The following types can be entered for a new drawing: AC - Acceptance (Usance credits) DP - Deferred Payment (Usance credits) RP - Release Payment SP - Sight Payment CO - L/C Collection The following types can only be entered as a change to an existing drawing: CC - Collection Chase CR - Collection Rejection FR - Final Rejection MA - Matured Acceptance MD - Matured Deferred Payment. RD - Registration of Documents DC - Document Checking AD-Amendment to drawings (only SP/MA/MD drawings can be amended using AD)

        SG - Shipping guarantee is issued under an import Letter of Credit. Can't be created manually. Draw type can be changed to SP, AC or DP only. For Drawing types of 'AC' and 'DP', a term or usance credit is established whereby the funds will be debited and paid on the MATURITY.REVIEW date specified later. If the funds are required to be paid before this date, the Drawing can be Discounted, whereby payment is made on the Value date specified, but reimbursement is obtained on the MATURITY.REVIEW date. If 'SP' is entered, then both Payment and reimbursement is made on the VALUE.DATE specified. For 'AC' and 'DP' type drawings, once the maturity review date is reached and the drawing undergoes maturity processing, then the Drawing type will automatically change to 'MA' (From 'AC'), and 'MD' (From 'DP'), indicating that these deals are now matured. However, it is to be noted that for Export Usance Drawing to Mature automatically, either the CONFIRM.INST in LC should hold the value as CONFIRM or the Drawing must have been discounted. In absence of either of these the Drawing has to be manually matured. In the case of Import Usance Drawing is maturity is always automatic with an option for the user to manually mature the same. If an authorised 'CO' is changed to a 'CC', then the system will perform chasing logic (ie. produce chase advices), and the reset the drawing type back to its original value, once authorised. When a drawing type of RP is used for an Export LC, this will generate a message (MT754) acknowledging documents were presented in accordance with the terms and conditions of the underlying credit and also a claim for reimbursement (MT742). Alternatively, an Import LC will generate the release of a payment, to the beneficiary, in the form of a Customer Transfer (MT100). A Final Rejection (FR) is normally used when the Sender considers the documents, not to be in accordance with the terms and conditions of the credit, and consequently, refuses them. The difference between drawing type FR and CR is that using type CR will generate a message denoting advice of refusal (MT734) and FR will only ever generate a letter denoting Advice of Refusal/Rejection (1734). Note that this drawing type may only be used following a Collection Rejection (CR). Amendment to Drawing (AD) is permitted to facilitate messaging activity by enabling to alter text and/or local fields.

        When the field REDUCE.LC.LIAB in MD.PARAMETER is set to 'Yes', 'SG' type of Drawings are created under import LC. Can't be created manually. Draw type can be changed to SP, AC or DP only. Note : Neither a type FR or RP will reduce Drawings limits. Validation Rules: 2-2 type AAA (Alpha) characters. Valid codes are: 'AC'; 'DP'; 'RP'; 'SP'; 'CO'; 'CC'; 'CR'; 'FR'; 'MA'; 'MD';'AD'. (Mandatory Input) RP may be used irrespective of the type of the underlying LC. If the type of L/C is a sight payment, then the only valid inputs to this field are:- 'SP', 'CO', 'CC', or 'CR'. If the type of L/C is a usance or term payment, then the only valid inputs to this field are:- 'AC', 'DP', 'CO', 'CC', or 'CR'. 'CR' can only be entered if the drawing has been previously authorised as 'CO'. 'FR' can only be entered if the drawing has previously been authorised as 'CR'. Next stage after registering documents "RD" must be "DC". Draw type "DC" can be changed to "CR","RP","SP","AC","DP" depending upon the LC type

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setFurtherId

        public void setFurtherId(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for FurtherId
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field further identifies the purpose of MT752 and is mapped to Tag 23. One of the following codes must be used: ACCEPT Conveys an authorization to accept a draft. DEBIT Conveys an authorization to debit the account of the issuing bank. NEGOTIATE Conveys an authorization to negotiate the documents with discrepancies in those cases where the original credit provides no specific reimbursement instructions or payment provisions. REIMBURSE Conveys an authorization to the presenting bank to claim reimbursement. REMITTED Is used to pay the presenting bank. SEE72 Conveys an authorization and/or payment which is a mixture of the above, or a special version of one of them and the conditions are explained in field 72. Validation Rules: Must be a valid SWIFT.CODE.WORDS with MESSAGE.TYPE as 23.

      • setGraceDays

        public void setGraceDays(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for GraceDays
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This is a Numeric field and shall be used to input to indicate the additional number of days for which the interest on the discounted drawing is to be recovered. This amount thus calculated for the number of days input in this field, will be in addition to the Discount and Load amount calculated. This field thus represents the cushion that could be made available in the event of the settlement being delayed for a Discounted Drawing. This shall however have no impact on the Maturity Date of the Drawing. Amortization of amount thus collected shall take place only till the MATURITY.REVIEW date or the NEW.MATURITY.DATE as input. In the event of such Discounted Drawing being extended using DR.DISC.AMENDMENTS, the amortization shall take place till the NEW.MATURITY.DATE. However, if the same is matured online or back-dated, then the amortization would have taken place only till such date. The input in this field is permitted only at the first instance of discounting a Drawing. The field opens up only if the Discount/Load rate is input. Validation Rules: Numeric field.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setIntermedBank

        public void setIntermedBank(java.lang.CharSequence param, int idx)
        Set the specified IntermedBank to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used to specify an intermediary bank through which funds are to be routed. If this field is entered, then a payment instruction will be generated to the Nostro payment account, instructing them to route the funds through this account, to the ACCOUNT.WITH bank identified below. Validation Rules: 1-35 type S (Uppercase alpha or numeric) characters. Can be free format name of intermediary bank or a customer id from the customer file. (Optional input) If entered, then ACCOUNT.WITH must be entered. The Intermediary bank must not be the same as the advising bank, the issuing bank, the third party bank, or the advise thru bank.

        Parameters:
        param - the IntermedBank to append
        idx - the position in collection
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setLimitReference

        public void setLimitReference(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for LimitReference
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field will identify the LIMIT.REFERENCE number to be checked for limit control on L/C transactions. Each Drawing transaction will be checked against the LIMIT file to verify the availability of a limit facility. If no input is made at this field, the LIMIT system will provide a default according to the values defined in the LIMIT.PARAMETER file. If required, more details can be found in the LIMIT user guide. A Sight drawing / Maturing Acceptance or Deferred Payment will result in the limit availability being increased by the amount of the payment. An Acceptance / Deferred Payment drawing will not impact the limit utilisation until its maturity. Note : The customer that limits will be checked against is the customer defined in CON.CUS.LINK (defined on the L/C record). Validation Rules: 3-7 numeric characters. Input to this field must be a valid LIMIT.REFERENCE number. If no limit exists for the customer, a corresponding error message will be displayed by the system with an override facility.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setLiquidationMode

        public void setLiquidationMode(TField value)
        Set the specified value for LiquidationMode
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field identifies the manner in which overdue payments are handled. The default for all contracts is AUTOMATIC. Three options are currently available: AUTOMATIC, SEMI-AUTOMATIC, and MANUAL AUTOMATIC indicates that payments will be settled irrespective of whether funds are available in the drawdown account. SEMI-AUTOMATIC indicates that a payment will be made only if funds are available, and that a PD end of day process will regularly attempt to make payment by checking whether funds have become available. MANUAL indicates that the contract will only settle if funds are available and that any future settlement of outstanding payments must be made manually via the PD module. Validation Rules: If the PD product is not defined for the current company then the only allowed setting is AUTOMATIC.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setLiquidationMode

      • setLoadAmount

        public void setLoadAmount(TField value)
        Set the specified value for LoadAmount
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Optional and only allowed if DISCOUNT.RATE or DISCOUNT.AMOUNT is present. This field together with DISCOUNT.AMT gives the total amount that the Document amount is to be discounted by, which should not exceed the document amount. If this field is entered, then payment will be made to the beneficiary, on the value date of the drawing, for the document amount minus the discount amount entered above, and the load amount entered here, if the Discount Party Charged is Beneficiary. Any charges for the account of the beneficiary will be deducted the net payment amount (i.e. document amount less discount and load amounts). Similarly, the reimbursement would be claimed for the document amount plus the discount amount entered above, and the load amount entered here, if the Discount Party Charged is Opener. The load amount will be accrued over the life of the drawing, at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file, separately from the discount amount. Drawings can be discounted in respect of Export/Import Letter of Credit. If the user wishes to enter a load rate rather than a load amount, then this can be performed by entering a value in the LOAD.RATE field above. Validation Rules: 1-14 type AMT (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point. Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is 'AC', or 'DP' and DISCOUNT.RATE, or DISCOUNT.AMT has been entered. If entered, then LOAD.RATE cannot be entered.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setLoadRate

        public void setLoadRate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for LoadRate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Allowed if DISCOUNT.RATE or DISCOUNT.AMOUNT is present. This field together with DISCOUNT.RATE gives the total rate that the Document amount is to be discounted by which should not exceed 100%. If this field is entered, then payment will be made to the beneficiary, on the value date of the drawing, for the document amount minus the discount amount calculated from the discount rate entered above, and the load amount calculated from the rate entered here, if the Discount Party Charged is Beneficiary. Any charges for the account of the beneficiary will be deducted the net payment amount (i.e. document amount less discount and load amounts). Similarly, if the reimburse were to be claimed from the Opener, the same is done for the document amount plus the discount amount calculated from the discount rate entered above, and the load amount calculated from the rate entered here, if the Discount Party Charged is Opener. The load amount will be accrued over the life of the drawing, at the frequency specified in the LC.PARAMETERS file, separately from the discount amount. Drawings can be discounted in respect of Export/Import Letter of Credit. If the user wishes to enter a load amount rather than a load rate, then this can be performed by entering a value in the LOAD.AMT field below. Validation Rules: Standard rate format (Only up to 6 integer and decimal characters). (Optional input) Can only be entered if the DRAWING.TYPE is 'AC', or 'DP' and DISCOUNT.RATE or DISCOUNT.AMT has been entered. If entered, then LOAD.AMT cannot be entered.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setMaturityReview

        public void setMaturityReview(TField value)
        Set the specified value for MaturityReview
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field contains the date on which Acceptance/Deferred Payment drawings will mature, or Letter of Credit Collection drawings will be due for chasing. For Sight drawings this field is to be used when Discounted, indicating the date up to which interest is to be calculated, when a rate is input. However, this field can be input only when DR.DEBIT.TO.CUST is set to NOTDEBITED for Sight Drawings. When a term/usance drawing is entered, the date in this field will be the date that maturity entries will be generated, and limits liquidated. These entries will be generated at the end of day on the date entered. For L/C Collection, this date will be used for chasing and following up the fate of the drawing. There will be an end of day report produced which which will list all collection type drawings that have passed their Maturity Review date. Validation Rules: Standard Date Format. Mandatory for drawing types: 'AC', 'DP', 'CO', 'CC'. Mandatory when Sight Drawing is discounted. No input allowed for drawing type 'SP' when not discounted. If a 'CO' is changed to a 'CC', then the user is requested to change this maturity review date to indicate the date the drawing should next be chased.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setMt732BkToBk

        public void setMt732BkToBk(TField param, int idx)
        Set the specified Mt732BkToBk to a specific position in collection.

        public void setNumberOfDays(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for NumberOfDays
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: The value entered here will be spread (number of days from value date to maturity date) used in calculation of a Discount/Load amount. This value is calculated by the system. If a value is entered, then the formula to calculate the discount amount from the discount rate will be calculated as: Discount Rate Spread Discount Amount = ---------------- * ------- 100 Basis Where: Discount Rate - Value entered in DISCOUNT.RATE Basis - Day basis from L/C contract. Spread - (Maturity Review Date - Value Date) + NO.OF.DAYS, which is calculated by the system. Validation Rules: 2 numeric characters. (Optional input) Value can only be entered if Discount Rate is entered.

        value - The value to set
