      • setOverride

        public void setOverride(java.lang.CharSequence param, int idx)
        Set the specified Override to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: System maintained field. This field contains all the override messages which the user agreed to during input of the Drawing. The field will be updated by the system and no operator input will be allowed. During the validation of a Drawing contract, the system may provide the user with a series of screen override messages to indicate an anomaly, for instance, that there is no limit set up for the customer. In the event that the user confirms the override, the full text of the actual override message will be stored, for reference purposes only, in this multivalue field. For example, if the user inputs a deal, then when the Drawing is validated a warning bell will sound and a message will appear at the foot of the screen which reads : 'NO LIMIT DEFINED FOR CUSTOMER' This will draw the users attention to the override entry(s). After checking and making any necessary amendments the user then approves the transaction. Validation Rules: This is a multi valued field. Standard T24 alphanumeric field. A maximum of 35 characters may be entered. This is a NOINPUT field.

        Parameters:
        param - the Override to append
        idx - the position in collection
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setPaymentAccount

        public void setPaymentAccount(TField value)
        Set the specified value for PaymentAccount
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field identifies the account where funds are to be paid to under this drawing. The account which will be credited on either the value date or maturity review date, depending on drawing type, for the payment in respect of the drawing. If the payment method entered above is either 'BP' (Bankers payment) or 'CH' (Cheque), then this field will be automatically updated by the system to indicate the account to be used. This will be set up on the LC.PARAMETERS file as 'B.P.ISSUED.ACC' and 'CHEQUES.ISSUE.ACC'. For drawing types 'AC', 'DP', this account will be credited on the Maturity Review date in respect of payment, unless the drawing is being discounted, in which case it will be credited on the value date. For drawing type 'SP', this account will be credited on the Value date in respect of payment. For drawing type 'CO' with 'UNDER.RESERVE' set to 'YES', then this account will be credited on the value date. Validation Rules: 1-16 Mnemonic characters relating to a Customer Account or a Nostro Account, or any other account. Default from Payment Method (see below). Mandatory input for Drawing types 'AC', 'DP', 'SP', and 'CO' with UNDER.RESERVE set to 'YES'.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setPaymentAmount

        public void setPaymentAmount(TField value)
        Set the specified value for PaymentAmount
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: System maintained field. This field displays the actual payment amount, less any charges and discount applicable, credited to the payment account. This field will be updated by the system when the credit to the payment account is made. On value date for 'SP' and discounted 'AC' or 'DP', or 'CO' Paid Under Reserve drawings, and on the Maturity Review date for non-discounted 'AC' and 'DP' drawings. The amount will be the full document or equivalent if a foreign exchange rate has been issued, amount, expressed in the currency of the payment account, minus any charges and discount and load amounts. Validation Rules: 1-14 type AMT (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point. This is a NOINPUT field.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field specifies either the details of the individual transaction or a reference to another message containing the details which are to be transmitted to the beneficiary customer. ROC Ordering customer's reference. The information specified in this field is intended only for the beneficiary customer, i.e., this information only needs to be conveyed by the Receiver.       • setPayresParty

        public void setPayresParty(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for PayresParty
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field cannot be input. It defaults to the party mentioned in the RISK.PARTY field of the Discrepant type chosen above. Eg : If the RISK.PARTY field in the DISCREPANT.TYPE table is PRESENTOR then the Presentor Customer number is defaulted as the PAYRES.PARTY or if the field has ISSUING.BANK as the RISK.PARTY then, the Issuing bank is defaulted as the PAYRES.PARTY. Explanation : The ultimate purpose of setting this field is to identify the actual Risk party of the particular transaction. Once this field is set, a separate Drawing Limit is hit for the party in this field and a contingent entry is raised for the party with type as PAYRES. Once the documents under collection are Accepted by the ISSUING.BANK, the Limits are reversed and the Contingent entry raised is also reversed and the normal flow continues from there on. Validation Rules: : It is a No input field. Defaults to the value in RISK.PARTY field in the DISCREPANT.TYPE chosen.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setProvAmtRel

        public void setProvAmtRel(TField value)
        Set the specified value for ProvAmtRel
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used to display the provision amount released on account of this DRAWING. Generally will be defaulted by the system based on the percentage of PROVISION input in LC. This will be in the currency in which the provision is held ( Provision credit account currency in LC contract). The field can also be input by the user as to the amount required to be released on account of this DRAWING. Validation Rules: Optional input. When input the amount will be checked with the provision percentage in LC and an error will be returned if the amount released exceeds the calculated amount. For calculation of the credit currency equivalent the following rules will be used. : The percentage in LC record is referred and the maximum release amount is determined. The amount determined is converted to credit provision currency using the current cross rate or mid rate.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Determines whether proportionate provision amount released is to be netted with Drawings amount at the time of settlement of Drawings. Example: LC Amount USD 100,000; Provision Percentage 20%; Provision Amount USD 20,000 Drawings Amount USD 50,000; Provision Netting Yes.

        DrCredit Provision AccountUSD 10,000
        Dr Drawdown AccountUSD 40,000
        CrPayment Account

        USD 50,000

        Validation Rules: Defaulted from PROV.NETTING field in LC.PARAMETERS. User can amend the defaulted value. Applicable only for LC's with provision.

        Set the specified value for RateBooked
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field displays the exchange rate quoted by the treasury department to the trade finance department (ie excluding department spread). When the document currency <DRAW.CURRENCY> and debit account currency <DRAWDOWN.ACCOUNT.CURRENCY> differ, the user will be able to insert an exchange rate to be applied <DEBIT.CUST.RATE>. This <DEBIT.CUST.RATE> can be derived from the departmental spread indicated in <RATE.SPREAD> and the treasury rate displayed in this <RATE.BOOKED> field.         Field description: This field specifies the reason for non-payment. This is a Mandatory field in the MT744 message. This field corresponds to field 73R in the messages. INSU Insufficient information in the claim (for example, payment instruction in complete, shipment data missing). NAUT Not authorised by Issuing Bank to reimburse. OTHR Any other reason which must be specified in the text (2nd subfield). OVER Total claim exceeds maximum documentary credit amount (exceed any additional amounts covered). REFE Refer to Issuing Bank for further instructions. TTNA TT claim not allowed. WINF Information stated in the claim differ from the R/A. XAMT Total claim exceeds available documentary credit amount (sum of maximum credit amount and additional amounts covered). Validation Rules: 4!c*35 line and accept Z (Alphanumeric) characters.

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is applicable only to documentary collections and indicate the date the collection should be chased. Accepts Standard date format.       • setTreasuryRate

        public void setTreasuryRate(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for TreasuryRate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This is an exchange rate between the document currency and the credit account currency. This is the rate quoted by the treasury department to the trade finance department excluding departmental spread. The department spread will be accepted in CUSTOMER.SPREAD field. The exchange rate including the rate spread will be customer credit rate and will be shown in CREDIT.CUST.RATE field. THE CREDIT.CUST.RATE will be applied between the document currency and the credit account currency (DRAW.CURRENCY and PAYMENT.ACCOUNT.CURRENCY) if they differ. Default calculated from currency table, using current mid market spot rate. Validation Rules: Standard Rate format (Only up to 6 integer and decimal characters) (Optional Input). Input to this field is only allowed if the payment account is in a different currency to the draw currency. Mainly used in export transactions, when the exporter's credit account is in a different currency to the document currency.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setTrustRel

        public void setTrustRel(TField value)
        Set the specified value for TrustRel
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is activated for CO type drawings under import Letter Of Credits. The valid values accepted are RELEASE, ACCEPT and REJECT. When this field is set to RELEASE, the system updates the trust limit and LC limit will be reversed back for the document amount. The static fields in Letter Of Credit will also be updated. The system also creates a contingent entry TRCOLL instead of COLL when the documents are set under REJECT. The system also defaults the draw type to be input by the user when he accepts the documents based on the LC type. In case of mixed payments user has to input the draw type and ACPT.TM.BAND field. When the documents are accepted, the user can change the draw type in the Drawing to AC or SP or DP (the value should be in NEW.DRAW.SET) the system automatically updates the TRUST.REL field as ACCEPT. Also the system reverses out the previous limits and contingent entries are creates new limit and contingent entry. When the user changes the draw type from CO to CR, this field is automatically set to REJECT thus reversing all the entries and limits created previously. The valid values accepted are : RELEASE, ACCEPT and REJECT

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Set the specified value for UnconfirmedAmt
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: When a Drawing is done under a partially confirmed Letter of Credit, the User has the option of defining the extent of liquidation under the Unconfirmed portion, which is input here. The input however cannot exceed the total amount unconfirmed under the Letter of Credit outstanding at that point of time. The sum of Confirmed and the Unconfirmed portion should be equal to the Document amount or the Liability amount whichever is lower. Validation Rules: Standard amount format. Mandatory when LC is partially confirmed. Automatically populated by the system when confirmed portion is entered.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setUnderReserve

        public void setUnderReserve(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for UnderReserve
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Applicable for Letter of Credit collection ('CO') drawings, when the documents are sent on a collection basis, because of discrepancies, but the drawing is paid to the benefiary "under reserve". This field indicates if payment for the drawing is made under reserve which enables funds paid to the beneficiary to be claimed back by the bank in the event that the documentation is refused by Opening Bank/Applicant due to discrepancies. This can only be entered if the drawing type is 'CO' and is an Export L/C, Payment will be effected on the value date of the drawing. Validation Rules: 'Y' or 'N'. Default 'N' Only allowed for drawing type 'CO', and Export L/C's.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setValueDate

        public void setValueDate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for ValueDate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field contains the value date for drawing entries. Can be future or back valued. The date entered here will be the date that CRF, Statement, and Category entries will be generated for this L/C. If the date specified is in the future, then the end of day batch of this date will generate the required entries. Validation Rules: Standard Date Format. Default to Today. Cannot be greater than the Maturity Review date.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing
